<TITLE> Sangakkara and Jayawardene lift Sri Lanka </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 SYDNEY, Feb 19 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Kumar Sangakkara and Mahela Jayawardene guided Sri Lanka out of trouble to post a healthy total of 238 for six in their tri-series one-day international against India on Tuesday. Sangakkara smashed 128 and Jayawardene 71 as the pair saved Sri Lanka from a disastrous start with a third wicket partnership of 153 on a scorching day at Adelaide Oval. India made a great start when they dismissed Sri Lanka's openers inside the first three overs. Tillakaratne Dilshan fell to a catch behind when he was on four then Sanath Jayasuriya was run out at the non-striker's end for a duck. Sangakkara and Jayawardene steadied the innings with a careful display, taking few risks as they set about building a competitive total. Jayawardene brought up his half-century off 74 balls before he was unluckily run out when Sangakkara played a straight drive off Praveen Kumar that brushed the bowler's fingers and crashed into the stumps with the Sri Lankan skipper short of his ground. Sangakkara reached his 50 off 88 deliveries then his hundred off 141 before throwing his wicket away in the last few frantic overs after putting his team in a strong positio
